fddiStatsTable.name: fddiStatsTable
fddiStatsTable.description: A list of promiscuous FDDI statistics entries

fddiStatsEntry.name: fddiStatsEntry
fddiStatsEntry.description: A collection of promiscuous statistics kept for packets on a particular FDDI interface.

fddiStatsIndex.name: fddiStatsIndex
fddiStatsIndex.description: The value of this object uniquely identifies this fddiStats entry.

fddiStatsDataSource.name: fddiStatsDataSource
fddiStatsDataSource.description: This object identifies the source of the data that this fddiStats entry is configured to analyze. This source can be any FDDI interface on this device. In order to identify a particular interface, this object shall identify the instance of the ifIndex object, defined in RFC 1213 and RFC 1573 [4,6], for the desired interface. For example, if an entry were to receive data from interface #1, this object would be set to ifIndex.1. The statistics in this group reflect all packets on the local network segment attached to the identified interface. This object may not be modified if the associated fddiStatsStatus object is equal to valid(1).

fddiStatsDropEvents.name: fddiStatsDropEvents
fddiStatsDropEvents.description: The total number of events in which packets were dropped by the probe due to lack of resources. Note that this number is not necessarily the number of packets dropped; it is just the number of times this condition has been detected.

fddiStatsOctets.name: fddiStatsOctets
fddiStatsOctets.description: The total number of octets of LLC data (including those in bad packets) received on the network (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

fddiStatsPkts.name: fddiStatsPkts
fddiStatsPkts.description: The total number of LLC packets (including bad packets, broadcast packets, and multicast packets) received.

fddiStatsBroadcastPkts.name: fddiStatsBroadcastPkts
fddiStatsBroadcastPkts.description: The total number of packets received that were directed to the broadcast address (0xFFFFFFFFFFFF). Note that this does not include multicast packets.

fddiStatsMulticastPkts.name: fddiStatsMulticastPkts
fddiStatsMulticastPkts.description: The total number of packets received that were directed to a local or global multicast or functional address. Note that this number does not include packets directed to the broadcast address.

fddiStatsErrors.name: fddiStatsErrors
fddiStatsErrors.description: The total number of packets received that had either a bad Frame Check Sequence (FCS) or a invalid data length. A packet with a invalid data length is one that is too short (length less than 21 octets / 42 symbols) or had an odd number of symbols.

fddiStatsPkts22Octets.name: fddiStatsPkts22Octets
fddiStatsPkts22Octets.description: The total number of good packets received that were 22 octets, or less, in length (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

fddiStatsPkts23to63Octets.name: fddiStatsPkts23to63Octets
fddiStatsPkts23to63Octets.description: The total number of good packets received that were between 23 and 63 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

fddiStatsPkts64to127Octets.name: fddiStatsPkts64to127Octets
fddiStatsPkts64to127Octets.description: The total number of good packets received that were between 64 and 127 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

fddiStatsPkts128to255Octets.name: fddiStatsPkts128to255Octets
fddiStatsPkts128to255Octets.description: The total number of good packets received that were between 128 and 255 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

fddiStatsPkts256to511Octets.name: fddiStatsPkts256to511Octets
fddiStatsPkts256to511Octets.description: The total number of good packets received that were between 256 and 511 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

fddiStatsPkts512to1023Octets.name: fddiStatsPkts512to1023Octets
fddiStatsPkts512to1023Octets.description: The total number of good packets received that were between 512 and 1023 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

fddiStatsPkts1024to2047Octets.name: fddiStatsPkts1024to2047Octets
fddiStatsPkts1024to2047Octets.description: The total number of good packets received that were between 1024 and 2047 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

fddiStatsPkts2048to4095Octets.name: fddiStatsPkts2048to4095Octets
fddiStatsPkts2048to4095Octets.description: The total number of good packets received that were between 2048 and 4095 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

fddiStatsPkts4096to4500Octets.name: fddiStatsPkts4096to4500Octets
fddiStatsPkts4096to4500Octets.description: The total number of good packets received that were between 4096 and 4500 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

fddiStatsTNEG.name: fddiStatsTNEG
fddiStatsTNEG.description: The Negotiated Token Rotation Time, TNeg, in nano-seconds

fddiStatsTokens.name: fddiStatsTokens
fddiStatsTokens.description: The number of valid tokens received

fddiStatsSMTs.name: fddiStatsSMTs
fddiStatsSMTs.description: The number of SMT frames received

fddiStatsClaims.name: fddiStatsClaims
fddiStatsClaims.description: The number of Claim frames received

fddiStatsDirBeacons.name: fddiStatsDirBeacons
fddiStatsDirBeacons.description: The number of Directed Beacon frames received. Directed Beacon frames have an FC field of 0xC2, a Destination Address of non-canonical: 80:01:43:00:80:00, canonical: 01:80:C2:00:01:00, a Source Address of this station, and a info field of 0x01 (Beacon Type) + pad field (0x000000).

fddiStatsBeacons.name: fddiStatsBeacons
fddiStatsBeacons.description: The number of MAC Beacon frames received. MAC Beacon frames have an FC field of 0xC2, a Destination Address of the null address a Source Address of this station, and a info field of 0x00 (Beacon Type) + pad field (0x000000).

fddiStatsBeaconAddr.name: fddiStatsBeaconAddr
fddiStatsBeaconAddr.description: The MAC address of the last station to send a Beacon Frame

fddiStatsDirBeaconAddr.name: fddiStatsDirBeaconAddr
fddiStatsDirBeaconAddr.description: The MAC address of the last station to send a Directed Beacon Frame

fddiStatsClaimAddr.name: fddiStatsClaimAddr
fddiStatsClaimAddr.description: The MAC address of the last station to send a Claim Frame

fddiStatsRingState.name: fddiStatsRingState
fddiStatsRingState.description: The current detected state of the ring. 1 Operational 2 Non Operational Claim 3 Non Operational Beacon 4 Non Operational Dir. Beacon

fddiStatsOwner.name: fddiStatsOwner
fddiStatsOwner.description: The entity that configured this entry and is therefore using the resources assigned to it.

fddiStatsStatus.name: fddiStatsStatus
fddiStatsStatus.description: The status of this fddiStats entry.

fddiStatsOtherPkts.name: fddiStatsOtherPkts
fddiStatsOtherPkts.description: The total number of other packets (including bad packets, broadcast packets, and multicast packets) received. Other packets which are packets which are not LLC, SMT or recognized MAC beacon packets.

fddiStatsOtherOctets.name: fddiStatsOtherOctets
fddiStatsOtherOctets.description: The total number of other octets (including those in bad packets) received on the network (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets). Other octets are those from packets which are packets which are not LLC, SMT or recognized MAC beacon packets.

fddiHistoryTable.name: fddiHistoryTable
fddiHistoryTable.description: A list of FDDI history entries.

fddiHistoryEntry.name: fddiHistoryEntry
fddiHistoryEntry.description: An historical sample of FDDI statistics on a particular FDDI interface. This sample is associated with the historyControlEntry which set up the parameters for a regular collection of these samples. As an example, an instance of the fddiHistoryPkts object might be named fddiHistoryPkts.2.89

fddiHistoryIndex.name: fddiHistoryIndex
fddiHistoryIndex.description: The history of which this entry is a part. The history identified by a particular value of this index is the same history as identified by the same value of historyControlIndex.

fddiHistorySampleIndex.name: fddiHistorySampleIndex
fddiHistorySampleIndex.description: An index that uniquely identifies the particular sample this entry represents among all samples associated with the same historyControlEntry. This index starts at 1 and increases by one as each new sample is taken.

fddiHistoryIntervalStart.name: fddiHistoryIntervalStart
fddiHistoryIntervalStart.description: The value of sysUpTime at the start of the interval over which this sample was measured. If the probe keeps track of the time of day, it should start the first sample of the history at a time such that when the next hour of the day begins, a sample is started at that instant. Note that following this rule may require the probe to delay collecting the first sample of the history, as each sample must be of the same interval. Also note that the sample which is currently being collected is not accessible in this table until the end of its interval.

fddiHistoryDropEvents.name: fddiHistoryDropEvents
fddiHistoryDropEvents.description: The total number of events in which packets were dropped by the probe due to lack of resources during this sampling interval. Note that this number is not necessarily the number of packets dropped, it is just the number of times this condition has been detected.

fddiHistoryOctets.name: fddiHistoryOctets
fddiHistoryOctets.description: The total number of octets of LLC data (including those in bad packets) received on the network (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets) during this sampling interval.

fddiHistoryPkts.name: fddiHistoryPkts
fddiHistoryPkts.description: The total number of LLC packets (including bad packets, broadcast packets, and multicast packets) received during this sampling interval.

fddiHistoryBroadcastPkts.name: fddiHistoryBroadcastPkts
fddiHistoryBroadcastPkts.description: The total number of packets received that were directed to the broadcast address (0xFFFFFFFFFFFF) during this sampling interval. Note that this does not include multicast packets.

fddiHistoryMulticastPkts.name: fddiHistoryMulticastPkts
fddiHistoryMulticastPkts.description: The total number of packets received that were directed to a local or global multicast or functional address during this sampling interval. Note that this number does not include packets directed to the broadcast address.

fddiHistoryErrors.name: fddiHistoryErrors
fddiHistoryErrors.description: The total number of packets received that had either a bad Frame Check Sequence (FCS) or a invalid data length during this sampling interval. A packet with a invalid data length is one that is too short (length less than 21 octets / 42 symbols) or had an odd number of symbols.

fddiHistoryPkts22Octets.name: fddiHistoryPkts22Octets
fddiHistoryPkts22Octets.description: The total number of good packets received that were 22 octets, or less, in length (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets) during this sampling interval.

fddiHistoryPkts23to63Octets.name: fddiHistoryPkts23to63Octets
fddiHistoryPkts23to63Octets.description: The total number of good packets received that were between 23 and 63 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets) during this sampling interval.

fddiHistoryPkts64to127Octets.name: fddiHistoryPkts64to127Octets
fddiHistoryPkts64to127Octets.description: The total number of good packets received that were between 64 and 127 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets) during this sampling interval.

fddiHistoryPkts128to255Octets.name: fddiHistoryPkts128to255Octets
fddiHistoryPkts128to255Octets.description: The total number of good packets received that were between 128 and 255 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets) during this sampling interval.

fddiHistoryPkts256to511Octets.name: fddiHistoryPkts256to511Octets
fddiHistoryPkts256to511Octets.description: The total number of good packets received that were between 256 and 511 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets) during this sampling interval.

fddiHistoryPkts512to1023Octets.name: fddiHistoryPkts512to1023Octets
fddiHistoryPkts512to1023Octets.description: The total number of good packets received that were between 512 and 1023 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets) during this sampling interval.

fddiHistoryPkts1024to2047Octets.name: fddiHistoryPkts1024to2047Octets
fddiHistoryPkts1024to2047Octets.description: The total number of good packets received that were between 1024 and 2047 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets) during this sampling interval.

fddiHistoryPkts2048to4095Octets.name: fddiHistoryPkts2048to4095Octets
fddiHistoryPkts2048to4095Octets.description: The total number of good packets received that were between 2048 and 4095 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets) during this sampling interval.

fddiHistoryPkts4096to4500Octets.name: fddiHistoryPkts4096to4500Octets
fddiHistoryPkts4096to4500Octets.description: The total number of good packets received that were between 4096 and 4500 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets) during this sampling interval.

fddiHistoryUtilization.name: fddiHistoryUtilization
fddiHistoryUtilization.description: The best estimate of the mean physical layer network utilization on this interface during this sampling interval, in hundredths of a percent. This is calculated as: utilize = ((bits/s used) * 10000) / (MAX bits/s) = ((bits/ms used) * 10000000) / 100000000 = (bits/ms used) / 10 = (((pkts * 5) + octets) * 8) / (interval * 10)

fddiHistoryTNEG.name: fddiHistoryTNEG
fddiHistoryTNEG.description: The Negotiated Token Rotation Time, TNeg, in nano-seconds at the end of the sample interval.

fddiHistoryMeanTRT.name: fddiHistoryMeanTRT
fddiHistoryMeanTRT.description: The Mean token rotation time. This calculated as the tokens received during the sample interval divided by the sample interval.

fddiHistorySMTs.name: fddiHistorySMTs
fddiHistorySMTs.description: The number of SMT frames received during the sample interval.

fddiHistoryClaims.name: fddiHistoryClaims
fddiHistoryClaims.description: The number of Claim frames received during the sample interval.

fddiHistoryDirBeacons.name: fddiHistoryDirBeacons
fddiHistoryDirBeacons.description: The number of Directed Beacon frames received during the sample interval. Directed Beacon frames have an FC field of 0xC2, a Destination Address of non-canonical: 80:01:43:00:80:00, canonical: 01:80:C2:00:01:00, a Source Address of this station, and a info field of 0x01 (Beacon Type) + pad field (0x000000).

fddiHistoryBeacons.name: fddiHistoryBeacons
fddiHistoryBeacons.description: The number of MAC Beacon frames received during the sample interval. MAC Beacon frames have an FC field of 0xC2, a Destination Address of the null address a Source Address of this station, and a info field of 0x00 (Beacon Type) + pad field (0x000000).

fddiHistoryRingStateChanges.name: fddiHistoryRingStateChanges
fddiHistoryRingStateChanges.description: Count of changes of the state of the ring during the sample interval.
